Roubaix Capital, a fundamental U.S. long/short equity hedge fund























Menu
Overview
Strategy
Management
Contact




Roubaix Capital, LLC provides discretionary investment management services to privately offered limited partnerships and separate accounts. Roubaix is headquartered in Denver, CO and is registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission as a Registered Investment Advisor.
Roubaix seeks to generate consistent alpha on both the long and short sides of our portfolios through the execution of a disciplined and repeatable investment process and strict adherence to risk guidelines.

Strategy



Fundamental Long/Short Equity Strategy
We believe applying fundamental research with a focus on smaller capitalization stocks uncovers unique long and short investments. Businesses that are less diversified are inherently more affected by the drivers that create or destroy equity value over the investment cycle. We have identified what we believe are the most important of these drivers as the strength or weakness of the business model itself, the pedigree of the fiduciaries, and the advantages or challenges created by the company’s financial structure. We look for these qualities and construct the portfolio within a three category framework. The first category is comprised of equities which have company-specific catalysts that we expect to generate returns largely independent of the overall market. The second category is investing behind themes that we believe will drive excess returns over time. Third, we have a portion of the portfolio that is expected to be driven by cyclical aspects of particular industries. We generally concentrate our positions in 40 longs and 40 shorts to maximize the value of our research and convictions, and likewise do not utilize ETFs. To manage risk, we avoid leverage, invest across a broad set of industries, and remain disciplined with our price targets and stop losses.Read more >



