Chris Hillary – Chief Executive Officer, Portfolio Manager
Financials, Industrials, Technology
Mr. Hillary founded Roubaix Capital, LLC (“Roubaix”, the “Firm”) in May 2015. From 2010 to present, he has served as portfolio manager of Roubaix Fund, L.P. (the “Fund”). Mr. Hillary was a founding partner and served as a senior analyst at Independence Capital Asset Partners, LLC (“ICAP”) since its inception in 2004 through its recent transition to Roubaix. He focuses his research on the Financials, Industrials and Technology sectors. From 2001 to 2004, Mr. Hillary was an analyst at Marsico Capital Management working for the Marsico International Opportunities Fund. Prior to Marsico, he worked for Morgan Stanley. Mr. Hillary is a graduate of Rutgers College and has a MBA from the University of Colorado.


Andrew Kalmar – Senior Analyst
Healthcare, Chemicals, Energy
Mr. Kalmar has been a senior member of the investment team since 2004. Mr. Kalmar also serves as portfolio manager of Calor Fund, L.P., a healthcare sector focused market neutral fund which launched in July 2012. He focuses his research on the healthcare, chemicals and energy sectors. Prior to joining the Firm, Mr. Kalmar was a high-yield analyst at Lord Abbett from February 2003 to October 2004. Prior experience includes summer internships at Price Waterhouse Coopers, LLC, Lord Abbett & Co. and Merrill Lynch Private Client Group. Mr. Kalmar is a graduate of Princeton University.


Mike Regan – Senior Analyst
Financials, Industrials, Transportation
Mr. Regan has been a member of the investment team since September 2014 with a focus on the financials, industrials and transportation sectors. From 2003 to 2008 and 2010 to 2012, Mr. Regan was a generalist equity analyst at Hawkshaw Capital Management, a small cap long/short equity hedge fund. Prior to this, Mr. Regan’s investment experience includes covering consumer equities at Copper Arch Capital and covering cable and satellite equities at DLJ, Credit Suisse and Deutsche Bank. From 2012-2014, Mr. Regan worked in Strategy and Innovation for Liberty Mutual. Mr. Regan earned an MBA from MIT Sloan and a BS in Finance from Georgetown University.


Bobby Jan – Analyst
Technology, Materials, Defense
Mr. Jan has been a member of the investment team since July 2014 with a focus on technology, materials and defense stocks. From July 2012 to July 2014, Mr. Jan served as a senior analyst at Oppenheimer Funds where he was responsible for derivatives trading, portfolio risk management, and competitive research. Prior experience includes being a private equity associate at SKY Roosevelt Capital in Dalian, China, financial markets analyst at Briefing.com, and lead research assistant at the Booth School of Business at the University of Chicago. Mr. Jan received a BA in Economics with Honors from the University of Chicago. Mr. Jan is a CFA charter holder and a member of the CFA Institute.


Beth Shanker
Chief Operations Officer & Chief Compliance Officer
Ms. Shanker was appointed Chief Operations Officer and Chief Compliance Officer of Roubaix upon its formation in May 2015. She originally joined ICAP as Compliance Manager in April 2012 and became ICAP’s Chief Compliance Officer in March 2014. From April 2009 to April 2012, Ms. Shanker was an independent legal and compliance consultant for investment advisers, broker-dealers and other financial institutions. From 2000 to 2009, Ms. Shanker was Vice President and Chief Compliance Officer for two distributing broker-dealers of ING. Prior to joining ING, Ms. Shanker was in the Legal/Compliance departments of MetLife and AXA from 1994 to 2000 where she provided advice on broker-dealer and investment advisor regulation. From 1990 to 1994, Ms. Shanker was an attorney in private practice in New York where she specialized in investment company, investment advisor and bank regulation at Rogers & Wells (NKA Clifford Chance) and Schulte Roth & Zabel. Ms. Shanker holds a BA from Barnard College, Columbia University and a JD from New York University School of Law and is a member of the bar in New York, Colorado and Connecticut.


Greg Parcella
Director of Marketing & Client Relations
Mr. Parcella joined Roubaix in July 2015. Prior to his current role, he served as Director of Business Development for Long Short Advisors, LLC, the distributor of an open-ended long/short equity mutual fund sub-advised by ICAP. From 2005 to 2012 Mr. Parcella was a generalist research analyst for three separate hedge funds engaged in long/short equity and event-driven credit strategies. From 2000 to 2004, he was an equity research analyst at Citigroup Asset Management covering the consumer space. Mr. Parcella holds a Bachelor of Science in Finance & Economics from Carnegie Mellon University.


Brian Montgomery
Fund Accountant & Operations Specialist 
Mr. Montgomery joined Roubaix in September 2015. Prior to joining Roubaix, Mr. Montgomery held a Financial Operations Supervisor position at ALPS Fund Services, A DST Company. Mr. Montgomery was also a part of ALPS in various other capacities from 2009-2015. Mr. Montgomery holds a Bachelor of Arts from Colorado State University and an MBA from The University of Colorado-Boulder.







